WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:23.562 --> 00:25.406
Okay, ladies,
this is the only cover-up

00:25.447 --> 00:27.822
you will ever need.
It is absolutely magical.

00:28.253 --> 00:30.142
And how much
does this magic cost?

00:30.228 --> 00:33.453
Well, if you ask me,
it's priceless, but for you, $29.99.

00:33.539 --> 00:35.384
Renewable every other month.

00:35.985 --> 00:37.751
Ooh, can you hold this?

00:40.164 --> 00:41.779
Ma'am.

00:42.478 --> 00:46.189
Marshals, is there... is there
something I can do for you?

00:46.275 --> 00:47.750
Your daughter home?

00:48.175 --> 00:52.017
No. She's at school. Why?

00:52.111 --> 00:54.189
We're gonna need to swing by
and pick her up.

00:55.719 --> 00:57.114
Can I get my purse?

00:57.208 --> 00:59.863
Just your purse. We'll come back
and close everything up.

01:00.689 --> 01:03.462
Sherri, is everything all right?
I don't know.

01:03.548 --> 01:05.525
- But are you coming back?
- I don't know.

01:05.611 --> 01:07.759
Well, can I still buy this?

01:13.123 --> 01:14.556
Is he here yet?

01:14.642 --> 01:16.337
Not yet. I just...

01:16.423 --> 01:19.665
I need to make you aware
of something.

01:19.790 --> 01:21.587
Unless it has to do
with Walter Franklin,

01:21.665 --> 01:23.033
I don't want to hear about it.

01:23.181 --> 01:24.704
Well, it sort of does.

01:24.872 --> 01:29.142
Uh, Taylor needed to bring
her son with her to work today.

01:29.314 --> 01:30.564
The heat was out

01:30.650 --> 01:31.790
at her day care and...

01:31.876 --> 01:33.642
Walter Franklin is coming.

01:33.728 --> 01:36.134
I know Walter Franklin
is coming. It'll be fine.

01:36.220 --> 01:37.156
Man's of a
certain age,

01:37.241 --> 01:39.728
I'm sure he's met lots
of children in his lifetime.

01:39.836 --> 01:41.290
- Little help?
- Sorry.

01:43.431 --> 01:44.884
Wha...?

01:45.649 --> 01:47.454
- Did I miss him?
- Uh, he's not here yet.

01:47.533 --> 01:49.259
Does, um, anybody
have a Sharpie?

01:49.345 --> 01:52.329
No. We are not having him
sign books.

01:52.453 --> 01:54.345
But-but they're his.
He-he wrote them.

01:54.431 --> 01:57.306
He is not here to entertain us.
He's a client.

01:57.447 --> 01:59.915
And one of the great legal minds
of the late 20th century.

02:00.001 --> 02:03.150
And Bull's hero. Mine, too.

02:03.415 --> 02:04.884
Any idea what he wants?

02:04.985 --> 02:07.040
None.
Just that he wants to meet.

02:07.126 --> 02:08.892
He has a case
he wants me to consider.

02:09.829 --> 02:10.846
I'm jealous.

02:10.931 --> 02:13.720
Mm. I won't lie, it's a bit
like having Babe Ruth

02:13.806 --> 02:15.806
- ask you to pitch to him.
- Mm.

02:15.891 --> 02:18.673
They just called from the lobby.
He's on his way up.

02:29.328 --> 02:31.808
Dr. Jason Bull,
I presume?

02:32.970 --> 02:34.665
Oh, my mistake.

02:34.806 --> 02:36.781
The folks at my firm said
you were younger than I

02:36.867 --> 02:39.259
and better looking.
I went with my gut.

02:39.782 --> 02:41.814
Mr. Franklin, it's an honor.

02:41.971 --> 02:44.470
You remember the
Arrowsure Corporation?

02:44.611 --> 02:47.986
The gigantic Ponzi scheme
that they had

02:48.072 --> 02:50.118
that the feds took down
a few years ago in Chicago?

02:50.259 --> 02:51.837
How could we not?

02:52.072 --> 02:54.406
100,000 people lost
their savings.

02:54.517 --> 02:56.517
The Madoff of the Midwest.

02:56.603 --> 02:58.251
You remember
Anthony Gibson?

02:58.439 --> 03:00.470
The mid-level accountant
that testified against

03:00.556 --> 03:02.361
the upper-level executives
in the trial?

03:02.486 --> 03:04.376
Of course.
Didn't you represent him?

03:04.461 --> 03:07.525
I did.
And now I represent his wife.

03:08.533 --> 03:10.635
As part of Anthony's plea deal,

03:10.751 --> 03:14.259
and in return for testifying
against his bosses,

03:14.564 --> 03:17.478
he and his family were put into
the Witness Protection Program.

03:17.641 --> 03:20.790
Moved from Chicago, Illinois
to Poughkeepsie, New York.

03:21.322 --> 03:23.526
Got a job in the
Highway Department.

03:23.970 --> 03:26.931
Two weeks ago, he was shot and
killed at 1:00 in the afternoon

03:27.017 --> 03:28.736
by a car driving through
his toll booth

03:28.827 --> 03:30.415
on Highway 11.

03:31.009 --> 03:33.720
Mrs. Gibson intends to sue
the U.S. government

03:33.806 --> 03:35.186
for wrongful death.

03:36.039 --> 03:38.126
The U.S. government.
Yeah, I've heard of them.

03:38.259 --> 03:40.712
You sure you don't want to
pick on someone your own size?

03:40.915 --> 03:43.572
Well, that's where you come in.

03:43.813 --> 03:46.150
Mrs. Gibson is a
tough customer.

03:46.283 --> 03:49.509
She's got enough anger for a
dozen lawsuits, and rightly so.

03:49.595 --> 03:52.026
She wants somebody to pay for
what happened to her husband.

03:52.345 --> 03:54.626
But you're worried jurors
might not sympathize

03:54.712 --> 03:55.720
with Ruth Madoff.

03:55.806 --> 03:58.283
Bingo. Guilt by association.

03:58.447 --> 03:59.728
And of course,
the irony is,

03:59.814 --> 04:02.587
he was one of the good guys,
a working stiff,

04:02.787 --> 04:06.845
one of 300 accountants,
just a guy making a living.

04:07.221 --> 04:08.939
But when the government came in

04:09.025 --> 04:12.435
and asked if anyone would
step up and testify against

04:12.521 --> 04:14.400
these ghouls who were
robbing the public blind,

04:14.486 --> 04:16.517
he was the one fellow

04:16.712 --> 04:19.408
who cleared his throat
and said yes.

04:19.930 --> 04:23.501
Felt it was his obligation.
Felt it was his civic duty.

04:23.728 --> 04:26.884
I get it, but I'm not sure
everyone will.

04:27.238 --> 04:28.876
It's not gonna be an easy sell.

04:28.962 --> 04:30.954
People hear you work
for Arrowsure Corp...

04:31.040 --> 04:32.246
I know.

04:32.634 --> 04:34.506
I assume this is
a contingency case?

04:34.591 --> 04:35.978
You really need
the cash up front?

04:36.064 --> 04:37.431
Look at this place.

04:37.517 --> 04:40.814
Looks like somebody went to Best
Buy for dinner and threw up.

04:42.047 --> 04:43.947
Come on, get a look
at this face.

04:44.050 --> 04:46.361
Don't you want to go
into business with this?

04:47.603 --> 04:49.806
Come on. Come with me,

04:50.351 --> 04:52.501
we'll visit the lady
and her daughter.

04:52.934 --> 04:57.329
Do some good with your life.
Earn yourself some good karma.

04:57.892 --> 05:00.259
My husband agreed to testify

05:00.423 --> 05:01.947
because they promised him

05:02.033 --> 05:04.345
that him and his family
would be safe.

05:04.431 --> 05:07.017
The government
made their case

05:07.103 --> 05:09.018
on my husband's back

05:09.104 --> 05:11.719
and then they just basically
left him for dead.

05:11.805 --> 05:13.525
How the hell am I
supposed to know

05:13.611 --> 05:17.353
that my daughter and I are safe
when that could happen?!

05:18.689 --> 05:19.962
You know what?

05:20.056 --> 05:22.314
I just need compensation
from the government

05:22.408 --> 05:24.723
to get me out of this country.
That's it.

05:24.814 --> 05:26.899
Just get me out of this country,
move someplace

05:27.031 --> 05:29.036
where everybody and his uncle
doesn't have a gun,

05:29.121 --> 05:31.126
so that me and my daughter
can start over. That's it.

05:31.211 --> 05:32.947
And that's what I'm here
to try and help you do,

05:33.025 --> 05:36.179
but take my word for it, you go
in there and demand anything

05:36.265 --> 05:37.310
from a jury,

05:37.396 --> 05:39.829
insult the country
they call home,

05:39.915 --> 05:43.000
and they are gonna be only
too happy to exact revenge

05:43.086 --> 05:44.934
on behalf of the friends
and relatives

05:45.020 --> 05:47.931
who lost everything to the
company your husband worked for.

05:48.017 --> 05:50.415
But, you put away that anger,

05:50.618 --> 05:52.970
and you go in
and present yourself

05:53.056 --> 05:55.231
as the victim
you actually are...

05:55.411 --> 05:59.072
The concerned mother,
the grieving widow...

05:59.377 --> 06:02.368
And you might just get
what you want.

06:04.133 --> 06:05.639
Walter, who is this guy?

06:05.725 --> 06:08.295
I... I don't like him.

06:10.973 --> 06:12.837
Give us a minute, will you.

06:23.243 --> 06:24.366
Who's in there?

06:24.452 --> 06:26.632
Daughter. Tiffany. 15.

06:34.650 --> 06:36.676
Tiffany, my name's
Dr. Jason Bull.

06:36.761 --> 06:38.837
I'm part of your mother's
legal team,

06:39.186 --> 06:41.040
at least for the time being.

06:41.995 --> 06:44.050
You think you and I could talk
for a second?

06:44.455 --> 06:46.251
You're not getting in that way.

06:56.920 --> 06:59.100
You have to climb through.

07:12.998 --> 07:15.043
What can I do
for you, sir?

07:15.621 --> 07:18.095
You're not here to take us
someplace else...

07:20.134 --> 07:21.517
are you?

07:22.283 --> 07:24.517
Maybe this wasn't
such a good idea.

07:24.603 --> 07:27.251
Sorry I dragged you
out here.

07:27.759 --> 07:29.724
Sorry I wasted
your time.

07:30.345 --> 07:32.076
You talked to the daughter?

07:32.290 --> 07:33.884
Said hello.

07:35.990 --> 07:38.470
If you ask me, we're repping
the wrong plaintiff.

07:38.954 --> 07:41.001
That 15-year-old girl,

07:41.728 --> 07:43.329
she's your case.

07:43.743 --> 07:45.318
Father turns state's evidence

07:45.404 --> 07:47.770
and suddenly she's yanked out of
the middle of the eighth grade

07:47.855 --> 07:49.739
and her life in Chicago
and dropped into a small town

07:49.824 --> 07:52.206
in New York
where she knows no one?

07:52.347 --> 07:54.503
14 months later,
in a single conversation,

07:54.589 --> 07:56.222
she's told
her father's been killed

07:56.308 --> 07:58.737
and she has
to move again to a motel.

07:58.823 --> 08:01.178
Cut off all contact
with everyone she knows

08:01.264 --> 08:02.699
for the second time in her life?

08:02.785 --> 08:05.557
The government that promised her
a safe, new home

08:05.643 --> 08:07.268
in return for her
father's bravery

08:07.354 --> 08:10.807
has delivered only death,
disruption and heartbreak.

08:13.125 --> 08:16.170
And what about Sherri?
What about the mother?

08:16.698 --> 08:17.711
My opinion?

08:17.797 --> 08:20.667
I wouldn't let her within
100 miles of the courthouse.

08:21.977 --> 08:23.776
